Status unknown; lived near GP antenna for long time; moved down past red barn in November 21; two detections (4/22 and 10/22) in current location; not added to Ghost Tag list - need field confirmation

Status unknown; some detections in same [long] pool, but most recent downstream movement was 170 m (more than flows could push through large pool?); not added to Ghost Tag list - need field confirmation

Status unknown; some upstream movement between detections; small fish that may still be alive; not added to Ghost Tag list - need field confirmation
Status unknown; three detections in one spot, then downstream movement of 210 m in October 2022; not added to Ghost Tag list - need field confirmation

Status unknown; Given size at release, fish likely matured and became a spawner in 2022; tag was probably still in a fish living in the pool below red barn on 4-20-22; could have spawed fall 2022 in riffle where tag has been found on 10-19-22 and 7-26-23. Need a third detection in this location to confirm (note high flows did not move tag between October 2022 and July 2023, so it should still be here if a ghost tag)
Not a ghost tag; upstream movement
Not a ghost tag; changed rivers, lots of movement

Likely ghost, Mature fish at tagging; likely spawned out tag in October 2021, though hard to tell if before or after 10-19-21 detections (not really a spwning location); best guess is that detection on 4-19-22 is spawning location in good gravel riffle (and ghost date), with downstream movement between 2022 and 2023 caused by high floods in spring 2023
Probably not a ghost, downstream movement too great

Likely ghost tag; likely died/spawned between 7-28-2021 and 10-19-22 (ghost tag date), with ghost tag moving downstream in spring 2023 flows to new location on 7-26-23; alternative explanation is that it was injured during tagging and drifted downstream into the "railroad hole" where it died prior to 7-28-21 (could be the ghost tag date instead) - not a lot of spawning habitat in the 7-28-21 location, so I kind of like this explanation better
Not a ghost tag; detections on RB downstream not consistent enough to say the tag just ot "hung up" on the antenna

Confirmed ghost; Big fish when tagged; upstream movement after release likely back to capture location; likely died/spawned between 7-28-2021 and 4-20-22 (ghost tag date), with ghost tag moving downstream in spring 2023 flows to new location on 7-26-23

Confirmed Ghost; upstream movement after release likely back to capture location; likely died/spawned between 7-28-2021 and 4-20-22 (ghost tag date), with ghost tag moving downstream in spring 2023 flows to new location on 7-26-23
Uncertain; ideally would have a dtectoin or 2 more
